                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d854">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.42793/1719: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-04T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >May 4, 1944—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>774. In private conversation yesterday afternoon Dr. T. V. Soong admitted to me
                    that Chiang had issued orders stopping all students <pb facs="1154" n="1140"
                        xml:id="pg_1140"/> and technicians from going to United States but said he
                    expects this order gradually to be relaxed. He admitted that the press report of
                    criticism of thought control by Harvard professors had had something to do with
                    Chiang’s petulant action. He spoke privately of Chiang’s present state of
                    irritation and impatience due to overwork and concentration in his own hands of
                    so many administrative duties which should be entrusted to others. While he
                    asked me to hold his remarks as private and confidential and not to be reported,
                    I feel the Department should be aware of present state of affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
